Turning her dark brown eyes to her athelfi she nodded.  &quot;Perhaps we should  allow each athelfi to chose the fate of their prisoner.  But, they have one week with their prisoner if they take them to Themiscrya.  I would prefer no males slaves in the city still.  They are dangerous and cannot be trusted...even when beaten into submission.  And any more time there...there is the threat of them getting away..and letting out the secrets of the city and it's paths.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odessaofpaphos>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#993300>(5/16/03 5:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=232>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prisoners</span><hr size=1> &quot;Pleasure to meetyou Tihari.&quot;<br>
