<br>
She brought it over to the campfire and knealed down.  Cleaning each bit of food gently to prepare it to cook for those who rescued her.  <br>
<br>
Finding an empty pot, Alexiares picked it up and tossed in her findings.  With a little water poured in, she set the pot near the fire.  Letting the heat slowely warm up and cook the edible plants of the forest. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 425<br> <font color=#993300>(5/19/03 5:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=234>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Tahira smiled to Odessa and then watched Alysia and the others from afar.<br>
