<br>
Then letting her go, Hippolyte seemed to reclaim her quieter side.  &quot;I believe many of us are finished here.  I shall stay the night and help those women who wish to leave for their homes..or follow us into the Amazon Nation.  From Themiscrya I can set them up to decide where they would like to go....for the Nation is large and strong.  They have many places to chose from.&quot;<br>
<br>
Just then Alexiares walked up offering some food.  Hippolyte allowed her lips to ease their harshness again.  &quot;Efharisto, I would like some and please...just call me Hippolyte...your athelfi.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solariwolf@amazonsunite>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Themiscryian War Queen</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#993300>(5/27/03 10:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=238>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack is over</span><hr size=1> Solari nodded as Alexaries offered her some food. Gently, Solari reached for some and was grateful to be eating. The pain was now gone, thanks to the liquid she had taken earlier. She sat there, staring into the fire once again, growing quiet. Her mind was slowing down, as was the adrenaline in her system. There was much to be done now, as she looked up at the families that had followed her and the others into the encampment. <br>
The families that followed had the look of scared animals upon their faces. Having just seen a group of women attack the men that had them 'enslaved' would probally scare anyone, Solari thought. Solari didnt hate men, as some of her other amazon sisters did; rather hated what some did to women. In some small way, Solari felt sadness for these women and the children, knowing that in the victory of being free, their lives were now beginning in a whole new way. One that would be harsh and full of trials. <br>
She turned her gaze back to the others around the fire. She thought about her own daughters, waiting on her back in Themiscyria. It was time for her to return to her duties. But not until Hippolyte was ready to return. She would make sure that her queen would return safely to the village.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alysiaofscynthia>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 427<br> <font color=#993300>(5/27/03 6:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=239>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ....</span><hr size=1> Alysia smiled as she took off after Hippolyte's hug.<br>
